WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good morning, Jacob. It's Wednesday, April first, twenty twenty-six. Happy

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
April Fools' Day — though honestly, the news has been

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
doing such a good job of being unbelievable that the

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
holiday feels redundant. Let's start with the weather and your

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
day. Jefferson City is looking at seventy degrees with showers

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
and thunderstorms, ninety percent chance of rain. Tacoma is fifty

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
degrees and also raining, because it's Tacoma. Your calendar: Karen

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
announces her retirement at eleven A-M — Q-2 officially starts.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
Then tonight, N-A-S-A's Artemis Two launches at five twenty-four P-M

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
Central. First crewed trip to the moon since nineteen seventy-two.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
Eighty percent favorable weather. Watch it from the couch with

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
your new carpet. Speaking of the carpet — it's done.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
Ben confirmed the installers left around one P-M yesterday. It

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
looks great. Your parents apparently showed up unannounced during the

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
install, brought snacks for the installers, and may or may

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
not have stolen something — or the installers did. The

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
texts are a little ambiguous but you seemed more amused

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
than concerned. Katelyn loved the photos. She also had a

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
rough night — went on an emergency run to clear

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
her head, said things were "pretty chaotic." She didn't elaborate.

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
Check in with her today. Now to the big stories.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
The Iran war is on day thirty-three. Trump told the

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
Daily Telegraph he's quote "beyond reconsideration" on pulling the U-S

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
out of N-A-T-O, calling the alliance a "paper tiger." Secretary

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
Rubio backed him up. France and Spain have denied airspace

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
to U-S warplanes. Italy blocked access to a base. Britain

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
is only allowing defensive operations. The Western alliance is fracturing

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
in real time. But here's where it gets weird: Trump

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
also said the war could end in "two to three

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
weeks." He claims regime change has been achieved and the

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
Strait of Hormuz will "automatically open." Brent crude briefly dipped

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
below one hundred dollars a barrel on the news. Markets

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
rallied. But his own advisers told Axios they have no

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
idea what he's actually planning. One senior adviser said, quote,

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
"Nobody knows in the end what he's really thinking." Which

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
is reassuring. Iran, meanwhile, is threatening to cyberattack Apple, Google,

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
Microsoft, and fifteen other U-S companies starting today. Happy fiftieth

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
birthday, Apple — here's a state-sponsored hacking campaign. Speaking of

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
Apple — it's officially fifty years old today. Founded April

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
first, nineteen seventy-six, by two college dropouts in a garage.

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
Apple updated its homepage with a rewind animation video. Paul

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
McCartney headlines the finale concert at Apple Park tonight. Employees

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
got commemorative gifts. And The Verge published its AirPods Max

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
Two review: incredible sound, still heavy, still five forty-nine, still

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
looks identical to the originals. Quick status board. D-H-S shutdown

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
is on day forty-seven. T-S-A paychecks arrived Monday. Congress is

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
on recess. No fix before mid-April. The Anthropic versus Pentagon

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
case has its appeal deadline tomorrow — the same day

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
as your pilot meeting at nine A-M. Review the Claude

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
pilot explainer note today. This is your shot. Also worth

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
knowing: Claude Code's source code leaked again — five hundred

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
twelve thousand lines — revealing a persistent background assistant mode

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
and, delightfully, a Tamagotchi-style virtual pet hidden inside the code.

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
SpaceX is holding April investor briefings ahead of what could

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
be the largest I-P-O in history at a one-point-seven-five trillion

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
dollar valuation. Microsoft just posted its worst quarter since two

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
thousand eight. Oracle is cutting thirty thousand employees to pay

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
for A-I data centers. And China's Baidu robotaxis simultaneously froze

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
on highways in Wuhan, stranding passengers — centralized A-I control

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
means centralized A-I failure. From Reddit: Sound Transit is considering

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
cutting the Tacoma light rail extension, ending the line at

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
Fife instead of Tacoma Dome. This is directly relevant to

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
your geography planning. The Tacoma subreddit is furious. Also, someone

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
on the Tacoma subreddit has developed an emotional attachment to

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
a blue heron at Wright Park, which honestly might be

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
the most wholesome thing in this entire briefing. Jobs: The

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
City of Seattle Economics and Revenue Analyst posting disappeared from

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
Indeed today. It may have closed. Check directly. King County

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
has a new procurement specialist role at one-oh-eight to one

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
thirty-seven K. Tomorrow is the big day. Anthropic pilot at

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
nine. Bill Review Training at two. Dinner with Alex, Chris,

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:48.000
and Dustin at six. Katelyn's off day. And the government's

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
appeal deadline on the case that will determine Claude's future

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.000
in public service. Here's where I leave you. Apple is

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
fifty. N-A-S-A is going to the moon. Trump is threatening

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
to leave N-A-T-O. Iran is threatening to hack Silicon Valley.

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
Anthropic accidentally revealed a virtual pet inside its coding tool.

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
Oracle is firing the population of Jefferson City. And tomorrow

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
you walk into a room and make the case for

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
A-I at work on the exact same day the government

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
decides whether to fight A-I in court. The writers of

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.000
this simulation are genuinely showing off now. Happy April Fools'

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
Day, Jacob. But none of this is a joke. Enjoy

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:32.800
the carpet.
